{"word":"H1082 - בָּלַג - bâlag - baw-lag' - Comfort","slug":"H1082","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">בָּלַג</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>bâlag"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>baw-lag'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Comfort"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D1;&#x05BC;&#x05DC;&#x05D2; - ba&#x0302;lag</b> - <i>baw-lag'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>break off</i> or <i>loose</i> (in a favorable or unfavorable sense), that is, <i>desist</i> (from grief) or <i>invade</i> (with destruction): - comfort, (recover) strength(-en)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1083\">H1083</a>, <a href=\"#/H1084\">H1084</a>, <a href=\"#/H1085\">H1085</a>, <a href=\"#/H1088\">H1088</a>, <a href=\"#/H4010\">H4010</a>"}]}